---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ScrollIndicator from '../../components/ScrollIndicator.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Solar Financing & Payment Plans | Interest-Free Options | EES"
  description="Solar and battery financing options including interest-free plans. Government rebates, green loans, and buy-now-pay-later available."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Financing Options</h1>
      <p>Flexible ways to pay for your solar, battery, or energy system.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Making Energy Upgrades Affordable</h2>
      <p>
        A solar, battery, or heat pump system pays for itself over time through reduced energy bills — but the upfront cost can be a barrier. We offer several financing options so you can start saving now without a large upfront payment.
      </p>

      <h2>Payment Options</h2>

      <h3>Interest-Free Payment Plans</h3>
      <p>
        Spread the cost of your system over time with no interest charges. You start saving on energy bills from day one while paying off the system in manageable instalments.
      </p>

      <h3>Green Loans</h3>
      <p>
        Several Australian lenders offer green loans specifically for energy-efficient home improvements — solar, batteries, heat pumps, and insulation. These loans typically offer lower interest rates than standard personal loans because they're secured against an asset that reduces your ongoing costs.
      </p>

      <h3>Buy Now, Pay Later</h3>
      <p>
        For qualifying systems, buy-now-pay-later options let you get your system installed immediately and pay in regular instalments over an agreed period. No large deposit required.
      </p>

      <h2>Government Rebates and Incentives</h2>
      <p>
        In addition to financing, several government programs reduce the upfront cost of your system:
      </p>

      <h3>Federal STC Rebate</h3>
      <p>
        Small-scale Technology Certificates (STCs) provide a point-of-sale discount on solar panel and heat pump installations. The value depends on your system size and location. We apply this discount directly to your quote — you don't need to claim it separately.
      </p>

      <h3>Victorian Solar Rebate</h3>
      <p>
        The Solar Victoria program offers rebates for solar panel installations on eligible properties. Eligibility is based on property value, household income, and whether you've previously received a rebate. As a Solar Victoria approved retailer, we handle the application for you.
      </p>

      <h3>Victorian Battery Rebate</h3>
      <p>
        A separate rebate is available for home battery installations through Solar Victoria. This can be combined with the solar rebate if you're installing both.
      </p>

      <h3>Victorian Energy Upgrades (VEU)</h3>
      <p>
        The VEU program provides incentives for energy-efficient upgrades including heat pumps and hot water systems. Rebate values vary depending on the product and your location.
      </p>

      <h2>What Can Be Financed?</h2>
      <p>
        Financing isn't just for solar panels. We can arrange payment plans for:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Solar panel systems</li>
        <li>Battery storage</li>
        <li>Heat pump hot water systems</li>
        <li>Hydronic heating and cooling</li>
        <li>Home automation and energy management</li>
        <li>Complete system packages (solar + battery + heat pump)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to Get Started</h2>
      <p>
        During your <a href="/services/consultation">free consultation</a>, we'll discuss which financing and rebate options apply to your situation. We provide a clear breakdown of total cost, rebate savings, and repayment terms so you can make an informed decision.
      </p>

      <p>
        <a href="/services/consultation">Book a free consultation</a> or call us on <a href="tel:0427664827">0427 664 827</a> to discuss your options.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <ScrollIndicator />
</BaseLayout>
